How to link local folder to your git repo:

create repo in in github
get https link for clone

create folder on mac
type
git init
git remote  add origin https://github.com/naqvisn/github-actions-test.git
got remote -v (will show they are link)

to push a file from vs code type in terminal after saving

git add -A
git commit -m "first change"
git push --set upstream orgin master (for first push only)

*** create a pull request: ***

git checkout -b develop
make change in file
save file
git add -A
git commit -m "pull-request"
git push --set-upstream origin develop
create a pull request
